-- Singapore's United Engineers unit sells auto business for $365 mln 
-- By Rachel Armstrong
-- Mon Aug 25, 2014 08:28PM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Aug 26 (Reuters) - Singapore's United Engineers Ltd <UTES.SI> said on Tuesday its subsidiary WBL Corporation was selling its automotive business to luxury car distributor StarChase Motorsports (Singapore) Pte Ltd for S$455 million($365 million).

The company said the sale was part of its plan to exit from non-core business operations. WBL, which is 67.6 percent owned by United Engineers, imports and distributes luxury cars across Singapore, Malaysia, China, Thailand, Indonesia and Vietnam. Oversea-Chinese Banking Corp <OCBC.SI> is in talks with a group linked to Thai billionaire Charoen Sirivadhanabhakdi to sell its stake in United Engineers. [ID:nL4N0QR2HE]